This paper focuses on the curation of Twitter user lists, which involves analyzing content and network information to generate recommendations. This falls under the category of social media analysis, which is often associated with sub-categories such as social networks (cs.SI), data mining (cs.SD), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computational social science (cs.SOC). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of content analysis, which could also place it in the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
